FBIS3-53067 "drnes007_k_94004" FBIS-NES-94-007 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Jan 1994 IRAQ Members of Presidential Guard Said Dismissed NC1001162894 (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan in Arabic 1500 GMT 10 Jan 94 NC1001162894 (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan in Arabic 1500 GMT 10 Jan 94 Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] According to reliable sources, Iraqi President Saddam Husayn dismissed Captain Sami [name indistinct], one of his personal guards from the Presidential Palace, in the past few days on a certain charge. Saddam's son, Qusayy, arrested Sami's brother (?Adina). Interrogations are being conducted of certain individuals who have connections with the captain. It should be recalled that the Iraqi regime arrested a large number of the officers in the Presidential Palace on 6 January on charges of collaboration with foreigners and the Iraqi opposition.
